More than 900 people were left homeless when fire burnt their shacks in Johannesburg’s Pomona informal settlement in Kempton Park, said Ekurhuleni Mayor Mzwandile Masina on Tuesday. <img class="alignnone wp-image-1228567 size-large" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=640%2C359&#038;ssl=1" alt="Fire destroys 400 shacks, 900 left homeless in South Africa" width="640" height="359" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=1024%2C575&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/IMG-20190723-WA0003.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> He stated that they are investigating what caused the fire which caused extensive damage on Monday night. “The cause of the fire is not yet established at this stage. “Three to four hundred shacks were destroyed. “No fatalities or injuries (are) reported at this stage. “Our teams are investigating the cause of fire and we should receive preliminary report soon,” said Masina. He said that 49 taxis had been provided to transfer people to community halls where “they are being accommodated and given the necessary assistance”. Masina invited civil society and faith-based organisations to help those affected by the fire. Vanguard Nigeria News The Police on Thursday said three people were killed during looting in Johannesburg’s sprawling Soweto township. August 30, 2018 In "News" Five people have been killed in a surge of xenophobic violence in South Africa, police said on Tuesday, as President Cyril Ramaphosa vowed to clamp down and the African Union, Nigeria and Zambia condemned the attacks. September 4, 2019 In "News" LAGOS — No fewer than 46 families were, weekend, rendered homeless and property worth millions of Naira destroyed, after fire gutted over seven houses in different locations in Lagos. September 1, 2013 In "News"